The Nigeria’s President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation on Monday, April 13, at 7 p.m. The President’s spokesman, Femi Adesina in a statement in Abuja on Monday, advised Television, radio and other electronic media outlets to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast. The President had on March 29 addressed the nation over the novel Coronavirus pandemic where he directed the cessation of all movements in Lagos, Ogun and the FCT for an initial period of 14 days with effect from March 30, to check the spread of the disease.